Attorney General to Seek Death Penalty in Unabomber Case
WASHINGTON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Authorities have movedUNABOMber suspect Theodore Kaczynski from Sacramento County Jailto a federal prison 20 miles southeast of Oakland in California.
Unabomber, the mail bomb terrorist, killed three people andinjured 23 others between 1978 and 1995.
Kaczynski is also charged with another fatal bombing in aseparate case in New Jersey.
Prosecutors say they have a great deal of evidence against the55-year-old former math professor, who's charged with four of the16 bombings blamed on the notorious UNABOMber, according to newsreports.
